< review>
Excellent authentic Mexican food, great selection of menu items, they also have an a la carte menu. I can't believe it took me so long to try this place. It is easily my new favorite place to get Mexican food in Eureka. My former favorite got too big when they started delivering and got rid of their a la carte menu. This place is definitely the best value for your money when it comes to authentic Mexican food. I had tacos al pastor, tacos de asada, and a chile relleno. Everything was delicious. All the meats were tender and juicy. The house salsa had a perfect balance of heat and flavor and they have a green cilantro/lime/avocado sauce that was really good as well. I can't wait to go back and try some of their other items.< /review>

<username>Lins Derry<//username><date>1497123150152</date><Rate>5</Rate>< Text>
I high recommend Danville Hardwood Co. They met every expectation we had. The crew was punctual and always cheerful. They finished our downstairs floor and stairs in only one and a half weeks but without compromising quality. We love the finished product! One of the rooms we installed the hardwood floors in is now my dance studio allowing me to choreograph and rehearse from home before going on solo tours. The floor can be hard and cold in the non-summer months so if looking to install floors for a yoga or dance studio, I suggest raising the floor. We are on a concrete slab. I give Danville Hardwood Co. a 10/10 both for craftsmanship and customer care!</Text>

<Review>I have remodeled several homes. I was in the market for new hardwood floors. I was lucky and was referred to Danville Hardwood. I met a man named Marc Bush who assisted me with every phase of my project. From our first meeting I knew Marc was a top professional. By first listening to my questions and concerns Marc made me feel like I was important. He helped me with the selection which took quite a long time. Trying to find the perfect product given all the colors and species is a daunting task. It never phased Marc. We discussed installation, including the removal and disposal of my old floors. When the installation crew arrived{ on time I might add} they went straight to work and transformed my home into a work of art. Leaving no detail unturned we even replaced our baseboards. Bottom line my wife is happy, I am happy. If you are looking for old school professionalism, a company who truly puts the customer first, you need to look further. < Text>
The hardwood floors in our bedrooms had been covered for years in old wall-to-wall carpet.  We got three bids on tearing it out and refinishing the hardwood underneath.  Dan Yorke wins the prize.  He showed up as promised, on time, and took in the whole situation immediately.  He advised us on what kind of baseboards would look best, gave us a choice of finishes (we chose satin),  what would happen each day and how long it would take.  Two days later we received  his bid, laid out as to what he would do, how it would be done, and carefully itemized.  One of the closets had a cedar floor and we wanted to keep that, so Cesar buffed the cedar floor to restore the cedar smell.  Miguel and his son moved all our furniture as though they were priceless antiques (they aren't). No bumps or scratches on the furniture or the new floors.  By the way, Cesar spoke perfect and fluent English so there were no questions or misunderstandings.  All in all, it was a great experience .  I'd use these guys again in a heartbeat and recommend them to anyone.</Text>

<Review>I'm sorry, but....

For any given pizza, crust can be good, toppings can be good, cheese is cheese .. but the SAUCE. The sauce is what makes one pizza stand out from all the others.

We fell in love with Fresh Brothers when they appeared in the South Bay in the early 2000s. For every birthday party, and many other times as well, we'd buy a few Fresh Brothers pies and they were wonderful.

But lately the sauce has just gone downhill.

I had a thin crust pizza tonight with chicken sausage and mushroom. The crust and toppings were good, the cheese was fine, but the sauce was bland and boring. Utterly uninspiring. The previous time I ordered a pie, there was hardly any sauce on it at all! This time, it was just flavorless.

What happened, Fresh Brothers? Did you cut corners? Choose a cheaper recipe?  It makes me sad, because for many years Fresh Brothers was THE PIZZA, hands down. It beat everything in town and all around. My daughter says" they're just not good any more," and I have to reluctantly agree.

Fresh Brothers used to beee our all time family favorite. Now, meh.<//Review><Response>None</Response>< Gmap_id>

Normally I would say that I absolutely LOVE Fresh Brothers Pizza! But this time, and perhaps it was just me, the pizza didn't live up to my expectations. They have changed the app slightly and now they charge more for a little extra sauce. I had never ordered more sauce  but this last order lacked sauce. The new era of "everything is in an app" with no access to human beings leads this reviewer left to leaving a review instead of having a conversation with a human being who could possibly make a difference. So, this is how it has to be I guess. The pizza was very dry and since their sauce is normally "to die for" and in this instance the sauce was insufficient (which since it was "take out" I didn't realize until I got home, which is 30 miles away...) i was left extremely disappointed and wondering if this is what FRESH BROTHERS pizza is now all about. <Rating>4</Rating>< review>
Quite possibly the best vegan pizza I have ever had. The Daiya cheese was fully melted and the choice of vegan sausage was delicious. They're vegan crust was also very well done, also I absolutely respect the fact that they offer the option for people with dietary restrictions.

I'm not vegan in any sense of the word. I love my red meat, dark meat, white meat, you name it. But I am lactose intolerant, so I was incredibly excited to have an option that wouldn't make me sick.

The only thing that I think could be improved is the presentation of the pizza, it definitely looked rather odd.<//review>

<name>8raddy<//name><Time>1577266656290< /Time><Rating>5< /Rating>< Review>
My favorite boba shop in this area! The boba tastes amazing and they have the best milk tea! I also tried the monster bobo latte since it was their most popular drink. It was a little too sweet for me but you can adjust the sugar level so I'd probably go half sweet next time. Staff is very nice and helpful and the decor inside is so cute! Definitely a bigger boba shop than most boba shops around. Lots of seating to study or hang with friends. Highly recommend :)<//Review>

<Review>The Ding Tea empire has finally conquered Fullerton in the form of the totally original name, Ding Tea Fullerton. Lets start by saying that I was a big fan of the decorations of the store that they took over and the fact that they pretty much kept most of it is a big plus.They also brought in a really large flower wall with the words Ding Tea Fullerton on it which is really pretty and aesthetically pleasing.

I came here once after seeing on my FiveStar app that I received a  BOGO Free coupon, and because my experiences at other Ding Teas has always been positive, I thought I would just give this new Ding Tea location a try. The experience here was the same, great drinks, and a fun environment to be around while waiting for my drink. The service when I came here though was okay. There was some sense of attitude and the utter desire of dissatisfaction but I blew it off. This was why I had to dock one star,

I would see myself studying here because, well, I used to study alot at the Miss 6 Tea that this Ding Tea took over, so why not just continue to study here again,< /Review><pictures>None<//pictures><Resp>None</Resp><gmapID>0x80dcd5938b19dbaf:0xe2d0ea042b34b411</gmapID></record></dataset><record>

<rate>2<//rate>< text>
Never have I been to a store that had so many employees on the floor that were so unhelpful to me. I went to this store looking for what I thought would be a relatively common item (brackets for mounting a windowbox planter on a railing). Upon walking in, I tried to talk to an employee to find out where this item would be, and despite seeing multiple employees nearby the entrance, they all seemed to be actively walking away from me, uninterested in helping. When I finally cornered some employees (who still seemed like they didn't want to be interacting with me), I was pointed to the same wrong aisle on the complete wrong end of the store several times. It was only when I went to the garden section that a (reluctant) employee pointed me to the correct section.

Even in the appropriate section, though, options were scarce. Despite having dozens of planter boxes in stock, the only appropriate mounting brackets I could find had obviously been returned (one was disorganized in its packaging and was missing parts, and the other was literally in a gallon plastic bag) and were not labeled at all.

So in the end, I did get what I was looking for, but the store and its employees felt hostile to me at every turn. I don't normally complain about employee service because I recognize that people don't have to treat me like their master, but when several employees avoid to me and give me incorrect information and the product is shoddy and disorganized, I feel like I deserve to complain. I will likely not return to this store if I can help it<//text>

I also dropped a very small little battery package on the ground right next to one of the Loew's staff who was doing something on a tablet or phone, and I had to lean down and get it while I was carrying two plants: she did not offer to help at all. < Review>
Wow! What an service!
Usually I don't have any preference for visiting Lowes or Home depot, but the recently experience I had with one of the associate here made me think about it.
Unlike other stores where we need to find the associate if we need an help, this guy came to me and ask if he can help me and even after helping me find the product, he was willing to wait and help me with other products too.

From now on, this store will definitely be my first choice over the another one.</Review>

<response>None< /response><rating>1< /rating><text>I got confirmation when I ordered awashing machine (on December 9th) that it would be delivered on December 23rd.  On December 22nd I got a call from the delivery company with a 4 hour delivery window - so far so good.  After waiting for the delivery, at the end of the 4 hour window, no one showed up.  When I called to see if they were running late, I was told that they needed a smaller truck to make the delivery and that they wouldn't actually be delivered that day... which no one bothered to tell me until I called them and they had apparently known about since the beginning of the delivery window!  But it gets better.  I couldn't' get any answer from the delivery company as to when it might actually be delivered, so I then spent over an hour on the phone with Lowe's (corporate, not the store itself, because after multiple attempts to call, no one picked up), who was in turn on hold with the delivery company, and at the end of the hour still couldn't give me any more information on when it might get delivered.  Lowe's then told me I should speak with the delivery company about getting some kind of reimbursement for my time, not Lowe's .  I was also told that the regional manager of the delivery company would be calling me by the end of the next day.  That was a week ago. I still have yet to hear anything from them.  So, I called Loews again... on December 28th.  I was finally told they could deliver it on Sunday (December 29th) and I should get a phone call later to confirm the delivery window.  At 9:30pm that night before the delivery, I get a phone call from Lowe's AGAIN saying they actually can't deliver it on Sunday!  After asking for a partial refund, I was offered $50 for the inconvenience.  I have spent 4 hours of my time, which I had to take off work for, waiting for a delivery that never came.  I have also spent several hours of my time on the phone trying (and failing miserably) to get any kind of answer about when it might be delivered and have experienced an immense amount of frustration in the process.  Apparently my time is not worth much at all to Lowe's though since I was offered $50 for the inconvenience (less than minimum wage at this point).  To top it all off, I STILL DON'T HAVE A DELIVERY SCHEDULED!!!!  This is a complete nightmare and I will never purchase anything from Lowe's again and will make sure to actively recommend to anyone I know to never order anything from Lowe's either if they can get the same thing elsewhere.  I could have ordered the exact same product for the same price from Home Depot or Costco - and they will absolutely have my business next time.< /text><UserId.>115442982074104516027<//UserId.><Pictures>None< /Pictures><username>Susan<//username><time>1577833524005<//time><gmap_id>0x808fcc098cc77683:0x7d8284a3f988ca14<//gmap_id></record>

<Review>I frequent many Lowe's / Home Depot and my experience here last night was amazing.

This store should be the model store for all Lowe's to follow.

Paint Section - My friend picked up paint and the worker actually asked what the paint is being used for.  She took the time to explain what texture is recommended and the difference between the prices.  Excellent!

Flooring Section - A worker came out of nowhere to ask if she could help and walked over to show where the items could be found.  Excellent!

Appliance Section - Jason came to help and took a lot of time to explain the many differences. When to buy to get the lowest price. Even showed the model rooms to show the newer colors and how certain sizes can look like.  He was very knowledgeable and really seemed to want to help!  Made recommendations and even mentioned which brands to stay away from.  Excellent!

Tools Section - Ian.  I don't know what he's doing here.  The guy should be running his own contractor business.  All I wanted to know was to know how to use my nail gun, but I walked out learning all the different uses for an air compressor.  Ian is VERY passionate about housing projects and it's very helpful to talk to him.  Super Excellent!

< review>
I went to the store at 6 am on a Monday. The employees acted as if they did not want to be working there and that my mere presence was inconvenient for them.   I came into the store to buy two specific items bug spray and batteries. I could not find the batteries and I circled the store two and a half times looking for the batteries that I want it. Not one employee offer to help me again they all acted as if I was in their way and an inconvenience. I headed to the front of the store and decided I wanted to look at the magazine and book racks, located next to the registers. There was a wooden pallet with product and my way making it unsafe for me to even shop in the area. The employee didn't offer to move the pallets he watched me as I climbed over.

After selecting a book I went to the registers to pay for my 3 items totaling approximately $60. No employees were at the cash registers which forced me to use the self help registers.  I had problems with the register because it did not recognize the batteries but I just bring up and it would not allow me to scan my next product. There was no one around to help me other than one employee you again after that if he didn't even see me and kept right on ignoring me. How does complete and utter frustration I walked out of the store and left my three items at the registers.   LOWES STORE MANAGER:  if you want to keep customers coming to your business I suggest that you open up registers in the morning but before you do that I suggest you train your stuff to be more friendly and to not be rude. Another reason why I absolutely despise big box companies such as Lowe's. One thing for certain I will not be shopping here again.<//review>

<name>Keith Gonzalez</name><Date>1544826181345< /Date><Rating>1<//Rating>< Text>
Dealing with this particular location has been an absolute nightmare. We have gone without an oven for over 4 months because of their complete incompetence. First, we waited weeks to find out that someone had forgotten to even place the order for our new oven. Then, after waiting again, we are told that they need to come take measurements before placing the order (why this wasn't mentioned earlier is anybody's guess). Finally, measurements were taken and the order placed. The oven arrived at the store and we are told we need to make an appointment for installation which ended up being a couple weeks out. Fine, whatever, we just need an oven, we already had to do without one for Thanksgiving. Today was installation day and we received a phone call one hour before they were scheduled to arrive to inform us that a 2 person team was required for installation which they don't have available today and the next available appointment is next Saturday. Tried calling the store to discuss this issue with the manager but she has already left for the day at 2pm on a friday. Given the way things have gone thus far, I doubt we will even have an oven for Christmas this year. Would give negative stars if that was an option.< /Text>

<Gmap_id>0x808fcc098cc77683:0x7d8284a3f988ca14< /Gmap_id><Pictures>None< /Pictures><text>I walk in the store and I'm in the need of a trailer. I've never purchased one before but I know what size I need. I see a 4x6 at the entrance but it's not the size I'm looking for. so 20 feet from the trailer I walk over to the cashier and ask if they have any other trailers I could look at. He tells me he doesn't know of any others. Standing in the same spot, in HIS line of site, I notice 2 other trailers sitting there. He didn't get my sarcasm, but I threw it his way anyways. "What about those?" I ask. With the dumbfounded look on his face he had nothing to say.
I walk over to the trailers and notice they're on sale and they are exactly what I was hoping for. I picked the better one of the two (one had broken light lenses). I go up to the check out desk to make the purchase but was told only 1 person in the store handles the DMV stuff. Of course, the person (John) wasn't there. She said he would be in in a bit. I asked her if he could call me when he got in, gave her my number and pleaded with her to PLEASE have him call me since we drove a distance to get this.
We tool around in the area for a few hours, no call from John. We go back to the store and when we pull in we see a fire truck, and an ambulance. i said out loud to my kids, "Watch, this will be thrown in my face!"
I go back to the desk (we're now over 3 hours into this) and I tell the person behind the counter we were expecting a call from John. Her reply, (with a healthy dose of attitude) "Well, you see what's  happening with the emergency vehicles out front, we've been a little busy!" And there it is... thrown in my face as I suspected. I wasn't rude or pushy, but may have had a slight bit of frustration in my demeanor as I was sympathetic to to whatever situation was brewing with the fire trucks. Apparently, John is also the only person who can handle emergencies, too!
4 hours into it, I'd yet to mean this Super John. finally, someone came up to assist us. I looked at the name tag and it said Juan. I thought maybe that was the John they were talking about. Then a few minutes later John walks up. I say nothing about the hours I've spent waiting for this transaction. Finally, hours later, we START the purchase. As I'm doing the paperwork I ask which one he is writing up, and noted that I wanted the one that didn't have broken lights. He said he picked the one he picked because the other had broken lights. Cool! I assumed we were on the same page.
Finally, about 5.5 hours from when I arrived at the store, we're done. I ask how the paperwork is handled with the DMV. He specifically told me that LOWE's would take care of all that and that I would receive the plates in the mail from the DMV. I confirm, "I don't have to do anything else, and they plates will be sent to me?" "Yep!' he says.
They tell me to meet them at the back of the store, at the back door where the trailer is parked and they will be right there. I drive around, wait 10 minutes, 10 minutes longer, then finally i see movement. Out comes the trailer. As we're attaching it to my hitch, I notice the light lens is broke. He tries to right the situation by grabbing a new lens and putting it on, which was nice. As he's walking away I notice one of the marker lights is also cracked open. I just wanted to get the hell out of that place! I didn't say anything about the 2nd light.
I wait a couple of months for the plates, but get nothing. I read the paperwork and it says it takes a while, and to call DMV if you haven't received the plates in 60 days. Well, i gave it LOTS of extra time... 5 months to be exact! So finally I call DMV. I give them the VIN number only to find it's not in their system. She asks me what paperwork I'm looking at. When I tell her, she is able to quickly decipher that Lowe's gave me completely wrong information. I was supposed to go to the DMV and bring the paperwork so they could register it in their system.
This place simply sucks!<//text><Name>Johnny Come Lately< /Name><Rating>1</Rating></record>
